Additional Notes: The %BIOME_MEAT% phrase in the Discovery Menu appears to be a placeholder that is filled in based on the type of biome this creature lives in.
Discovery Menu: Found on planet Cel-Nazaifus I, A. Ephemoegoe has adapted to the temperate climate and humid atmosphere. A patient hunter, their highly evolved sense organs allow them to detect prey at extreme distances. Carnivores, their hunger for %BIOME_MEAT% {{sic}} is never-ending.

Additional Notes: A rare form of a bipedal

System: What We Do In The Shadows

Summary Notes: This is a hovering/flying subspecies type.

Summary Notes: Encoutnered on planet Regyro, where they navigate caustic ground and choking acid rain. High growth hormone levels in their brains have caused an unusually dense neuron structure. What this extra neural power is used for is unclear. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Fungal Cluster that grow freely across this world.
Appearance: Resembles a giant bronze crab with eight spindly legs. It has two varieties: crab face with claws, and another with the eye stalks attacked to the body, a beak, protrutions on the back, feelers, and a thorax. It's notable feature is that it can float slightly above the ground.
Additional Notes: Traveller's Notes: Oh, I have an answer for that neural power: giving it's horrific ability to float in the air. It's a monstrous fauna of eldritch proportions. Thank goodness it's herbivorous, or I will start blasting. Because of the way it looks and the fact it floats, I've dubbed this creature "Crabthulu".

Summary Notes: Encountered on planet Regyro, where they live despite highly toxic conditions. Calm and methodical creatures, they graze the planet with an air of gentle, unflustered serenity. Their diet consists of fallen fruit that has begun to rot. This fermented, bacteria-enriched mush appears to have a vital place in their digestive system.
Appearance: Resembles a giant brown biped. The feet are long and cylindrical, with the thighs possessing a thick hide. Each feet has four digits and a fifth toe off to the side. It has a thick-hide on its back, with green spinal plates protruding out. It's tail is short, stubby, and splits in two. It possess a white underbelly that extends all the way to the lower jaw. It has two medium-sized arms, but appear vestigial. Its neck is long and the head is about as thick as the neck. The head itself is conical, possess no eyes, and has two flat horns at the ridge of the nose.
Additional Notes: The creature is a Megafauna, causing the ground to shake on every step.

Summary Notes: First discovered flying over the plant-filled landscapes of planet Takerm V. Carried by the wind as much as their wings, these small insects live a scattered and chaotic existence. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew up all but the most venomous of leaves.
Appearance: Resembles an incredibly tiny jellyfish with a flat body and thin tentacles, with a growth in the center of the body where the tentacles originate. There are two varieties: blue with a golden growth, and yellow with a red growth. Despite the discovery entry describing it to be 0.3 meters, it's so incredibly tiny it can only be scanned while it's moving, and cannot be seen regularly without the aid of the Analysis Visor to see where it is. It's so tiny that it's even smaller than the ambient "firefly lights".
Additional Notes: Due to it's absurdly small size, you're going to need to use the Analysis Tool to see where they're at, and it can only be scanned while moving. Walking near them causes them to move more. Despite the fact it has Sweetened Compost as its bait, using the bait does not attract them.
Discovery Menu: https://atlascodex.space/discoveries/fairy-jelly-j-windoximii/

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: Extremely cute. If I could adopt one, I'd take it with me, wherever I go. Please. Let me have this.
Appearance: It resembles a small, stubby amphibian with brown and yellow skin, and a mouth between the eyes. The Vectorised gender has eyes inside a dark-brown tube that surrounds the head. Because if its cute appearnace and squishy body, it's been dubbed "Adoraflan".
Discovery Menu: Adoraflan (V. Mustgeantia) is at home inthe toxic floods of planet Ogori. Their search for food drags them far and wide across the planet, their journey never ending. Their diet is varied, but they will gorge upon Fungal Cluster at any opportunity.

Appearance: It resembles a orange-yellow butterfly with an extremely long tail. The wings is that of a birdwing butterfly with cyan stripes and eye-spots. The end of the tail has a pair of wings as well. The tail itself is plated with chiten, except for the white underside. The thorax is the same as a typical butterfly:six small legs, armored back but a darker, exposed underbelly. The head has large compound eyes and a tiny proboscis. This species has no antennas.
Discovery Menu: Native to the skies of planet Ocullu Aido, where Nymphiptere Birdwing (Z. Brickhorysera) enjoys plentiful food and water. Scans reveal a nervous system of pure light; the inner lives are radiant beyond compare. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.

Appearance: It is a big crab creature with spindly legs and a hardened head. Its body is bronze with speckles of white. It comes in two variants: crab-face with claws, and six-eyed with large hairs and mandibles. The crab-faced variant has an extended head, while the six-eyed variant has a thicker head.
Additional Notes: Traveler's Notes: Reminds me of the Gammabrains of Nuuktas and the Crabthulu of Regyro, before both of them went extinct. Not to mention, this one is just a third as big as the other two.
Discovery Menu: Native to planet Paton, where they live brief and sweaty lives. Long-lived and gentle, their rich lives and complex society hierarchy allow them to develop wisdom that rivals technologically advanced species. They delve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for the Cave marrow.

Appearance: The creature resembles a giant, hovering green-brown mushroom cap. The underside is pale compared to the outer skin.
Additional Notes: Despite its rarity, they always appear in large groups.
Discovery Menu: Hover-Cap (I. Felimiquae) was discovered on the verdant landscapes of planet Japame. Their lives are painfully short, and these flying insects spend their handful of days in a furious quest to mate. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: Extremely strange beings with no discernable facial features, let alone biologically possible.
Appearance: It resembles a bronze, spiral-shaped shell. Each half is barely connected by thin connections at the rear. In detail, the shape is a conical diamond made of a chitinous material that's scored in the direction of the spiral. The inside of the shell is thin and plated. Each end of the shell is tapered to a smooth point.
Additional Notes: Two genders: Indeterminate and Vectorised. Both indistinguishable.
Discovery Menu: Discovered amidst the thermonuclear fog of planet Papleycit. Carried by the wind as much as their wings, these small insects live a scattered and chaotic existence. Though they have mouths, it seems their primary nutrient intake via their skin, in a form of atmospheric mineral absorption.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: I... I mispelled chitin and there's nothing I can do about it now. Also... I've heard of creepy-crawlies, but creepy-rollies? On top of that, what in all that is holy is that scientific name?! It literally means "blood demon"!
Appearance: It resembles a black, chitinous wheel. Each segment is an ovolar plate that is angled in a way to give the creature a grip on the ground as it rolls. Under the plate is a spinal vertebra that is also made of the same chitin that give the creature it's hoop body.
Additional Notes: Two genders: Radical and Asymptotic. Both indistinguishable.
Discovery Menu: Found on planet Papleycit, where they had adapted to the hot, highly radioactive atmosphere. Poor sensory systems leave this typically passive creature unable to precieve much of the external world. However, brain scans reveal a deep, rich inner life. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.

Appearance: It resembles a fleshy ball with 24 S-shaped tentacles, each tipped with a spade-like claw used digging into the ground.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Ogori, where they thrive in the chokingly toxic atmosphere. These simple insects barely have a brain at all and react to external stimuli only via localised reflexes. A highly specialised digestive systems allow them to eat the Fungal Cluster that grow on their home planet.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: A terrifying sight, let's be honest.
Appearance: It resembles subterranian amalgamation of yellow-brown tentacles that constantly errupt and flail from the ground. The main body is unknown.
Discovery Menu: Terra Kraken (H. Macrogayera) is at home in the toxic floods of planet Ogori. Submissive and gentle in their relationships with one another, they nonetheless respond forcefully when threatened by other creatures. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

Appearance: It resembles a redish-brown insectoid. The Prime gender has 8 glossy, spindly legs, an open back thorax, a spiked abdomen, and a long mantis body that extends from the front of the thorax. It has two long appendages that end with pincers, and two tentacles attached to the thorax. The head of the creature is similar to a mantis, with big eyes, flat ears, and two antenni. The Vectorised gender possess a closed back, a crab-like head instead of a long body, and lacks pincers but retains the tentacles.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Awktwenns, where they thrive int he chokingly toxic atmosphere. Possessed of a tremendous natural strength, they fear no other creature that walks upon this world. Comfortable amonst dense foliage, they sniff and scurry among fallen leaves, searching for the nuts that provide their food.

Appearance: It resmbles a greenish-brown insectoid. The Prime gender looks very similar to a Lesser Cancectoid: open back thorax, spiked abdomen, eight legs, long body, mantis-like head, and pincer appendages with a lower set of tentacles. The only differences is that its legs are covered in a carapase, giving it rigidity, and its eyes are envoloped by fused eyelid, much like a chameleon. It's also considerably larger than it's Lesser counterpart. The Asymptotic gender has the same thorax as the Prime gender, but has no abdomen or a long body extending from the thorax, and no pincers. Instead, it has two sets of two compound eyes, with a set of mandibles between them, and hairy, spider-like legs instead.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on the planet Awktwenns, where they navigate caustic ground and choking acid rain. Social animals, they show great care in tending to their young and their sick. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: You cannot tell, but my face is squinting and I am incredibly confused.
Appearance: It has no physical body we can see. It manifests as steam or smoke jetting out of the ground.
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet Beve. Scans reveal them to be highly intelligent. However, they are easily tamed and appear content to follow the whims of other creatures. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: My back feels vulnerable just looking at it.
Appearance: It resembles squid-like creature made entirely of bones or calcified material. The head is segmented into four plates that form an arrow, and behind it are four tentacles that resemble spinal vertebre. It Orthogonal gender is green, while the Radical gender is slightly paler.
Discovery Menu: Discovered amidst the thermonuclear fog of planet Beve. Without a centralised nervous system, these are creatures of pure instinct, pure reaction. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Gamma Weed that grow freely across this world.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: Despite the infection that has claimed this planet, seeing such majestic creatures is a nice change of pace.
Appearance: Resembles a giant, pink butterfly with blue accents. It has three pairs of wings, with one pair on top of the other two. Each wing is veiny and long like beetle wings. The back-most wings point directly backwards, while the other wings point outwards.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Gusiusia IX, where they thrive in the chokingly toxic atmosphere. Their lives are brief; their existence a blip, nothing but a single desperate flight. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly-coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: I can never get enough of these these butterflies.
Appearance: Remembles a giant butterfly with a pair of giant, triangular wings. Each wing has a black ring patter and white accents at the end. The back has a cyan streak that runs the length of the spine.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet Sitrick III. These simple insects barely have a brain at all and react to external stimuli only via localised reflexes. They snuffle for food with their noises dug into the dirt, flicking earth into their mouths with long, spiked tongues. Nutrient source is presumed to be soil-bound micro-organisms.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: Like flying sunny-side up eggs you forgot to throw away two weeks ago, and now it gained sentience.
Appearance: Resembles a yellow, amoeba-like orgamism with tiny tentacles. It has two genders: Indeterminant and Vectorised, and can be distinguished by the color of the core; red for Vectorised and brown for Indeterminant.
Additional Notes: Sporefly; actual height is 0.1, but even still it's pretty huge. Always appears in a swarm.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet Sitrick III. Carried by the wind as much as their wings, these small insects live a scattered and chaotic existence. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local fauna.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: I'd say it's bloated in power, but it's more majestic than powerful.
Appearance: Resembles a large, deep-purple beetle with rock-like elytras and gold-speckled face. It's exoskeleton is dark grey and its wings are a royal purple. The discovery menu argues that its genders is either Unknown or None, and sometimes returns a brown variant.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Sitrick III. Carried by the wind as much as their wings, these small insects live a scattered and chaotic existence. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly-coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: I want to ride one.
Appearance: Resembles a giant, floating eel-like creature. It's skin is dark grey with a tint of blue. It has a sail fin on both its ventral and dorsal side that runs the length of the tail. The dorsal side of the creature has a spotted pattern. It has two sets of fins, with the pectoral fins being larger than the pelvic fins behind it. It's face is rather monstrous: each side has three eyes, two long horns at the noseridge, and a jaw that splits slightly with two long fangs at the end. Inside the mouth is leech-like secondary mouth adorned with teeth.
Discovery Menu: Found primarily in the humid, muggy skies of planet Kuyrenden Prime. Curious and intelligent, their nests are stuffed with brightly colour rocks and slivers of metal. Some build elaborate metal structures, showing remarkable artistry. Their diet consists of fallen fruit that has begun to rot. This fermented, bacteria--enriched mush appears to have a vital place in their digestive system.

Appearance: It resembles a giant, green reptilian biped. It has a long, flat tail that extends further by two extrusions. It's feet remble that of a rhino, but with a vestigal toe higher up the foot. It possess a long muscular neck, and its head has three sets of eyes on each side of the head. It's notabily feature is its long, scooping jaw that overextends the lower jaw by a large distance. Both genders, Exotic and Female, have spikes that run along their spine, but the female lacks these scales on its neck and head.
Discovery Menu: Found on the planet Kuyrenden Prime, where the temperate climate and frequent rainfall encourage the rapid evolution of new lifeforms. Gregarious, wide-roaming creatures. They are occasionally found alone, but such animals are unhappy, lost from their herd. Delicate feeders, they nibble selectively at local flora, ensuring they never entirely strip an area of foliage.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: Oh, there's the tail.
Appearance: It resembles a giant ball of diamond-back snakes, with no visible end. In fact, everything looks fused together to form the ball.
Discovery Menu: Snake Amalgam (E. Elderumedium) was discovered in the verdant landscapes of planet Ancas XVI. Highly docile. This behavior appears to be instinctive, as if they have evolved to serve the whims of a complex herding predator. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.

Summary Notes: Traveler's Notes: As expected, its tears don't heal injuries. In fact, I feel bad for trying to make it cry.
Appearance: It resembles a giant, disembodied eye with very muscular eyelids and a single amber cat's eye that is constantly looking in various directions.
Discovery Menu: Found on the planet Ancas XVI, where the temperate climate and frequent rainfall encourage the rapid evolution of new lifeforms. Scans reveal them to be highly intelligent. However, they are easily tamed and appear content to follow the whims of other creatures. Their diet is largely conventional, consisting laregly of local flora. But the scent of Nip Nip drives them to a frenzy, and they will gorge upon its buds.

Appearance: This species of Bos floats across the planet surface at a small elevation.
This subgenus of Bos floats above the planet surface.
Hovers over the ground via very small wings.
This bos hovers over the ground.

Additional Notes: Conflict between discovery screen and scanner: Bait: Scented Herbs on discovery but "Ion Battery" on scan (for Mechanoceris)

Appearance: It appears to resemble geothermal vents.
Walks and stands as a biped.
Biped, walks on hind legs.
Hovers over the ground with small wings.
Walks as a biped upright sometimes.
Walks on two legs as a bipedal.
Eyeball bubble.
Floats above the surface.

Discovery Menu: L. Wailreyum was first recorded in the shattered remains of planet AGT Ruveykove II, thriving despite the nuclear storms. They appear to be peaceful creatures, happily socialising both within their species and without. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

Discovery Menu: Recorded in the highly-radiactive seas of planet Tesvill. Calm and methodical creatures, they graze the planet with an air of gentle, unflustered serenity. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.
NMS Wiki Link: H. Triromus - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Discovered on Tesvill, where they survive despite hostile levels of background radiation. These simple insects barely have a brain at all and react to external stimuli only via localised reflexes. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Gamma Weed.
NMS Wiki Link: C. Grantrombricii - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found in the gamma-drenched skies of planet Tesvill. These flying insects are drawn ever onwards by a terrible hunger, their hunt is never ending. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly-coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.
NMS Wiki Link: N. Posttudisima - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet Tesvill. Once they emerge from the nest, they never again touch the ground. Their lives are spent on the wing, their stamina unrivalled. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.
NMS Wiki Link: X. Feliscaabudium - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: First recorded on the uranium-infused atmosphere of planet Tesvill. Powerful lateral muscles allow them to take off with remarkable speed, taking to the air faster than any ground predator could possibly lunge. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Gamma Weed.
NMS Wiki Link: A. Gresseiea - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on the gamma-drenched surface of planet Tesvill. Scans reveal a nervous system of pure light; the inner lives are radiant beyond compare. Draw to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.
NMS Wiki Link: J. Heydranuvaldis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: E. Pavoharonica was first recorded in the dustbowls of planet Kakeg 29 S1. Possessing a calm intelligence, their piercing eyes never forget a face. A plague upon stranded adventurers, as they feast upon di-hydrogen crystals. Their highly reactive saliva dissolves the crystals without the need to chew.
NMS Wiki Link: E. Pavoharonica - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Kakeg 29 S1, where they survive despite the near-constant drought. Weaker than their appearance suggests, they make up for the many who die on their nomadic wanderings with frequent and rapid breeding. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.
NMS Wiki Link: Q. Mammanarotae - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on the barren plains of planet Kakeg 29 S1. Their muscles are held in a state of constant tension, ready to flee at the smallest sign of danger. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Echinocactus.
NMS Wiki Link: Y. Equuslamucis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Discovered amidst the grit and dust of planet Kakeg 29 S1. Scans reveal small neural clusters growing all over their nervous system, creating a highly complex distributed brain network. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Echinocactus that grow freely across this world.
NMS Wiki Link: E. Elecitrtechepima - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Kakeg 29 S1, where they survive despite the near-constant drought. Submissive without being timid, these gentle creatures know no fear, only curiosity. Their finely-tuned sense of smell draws them to the most beautiful, richly-scented flowers, which they then consume whole.
NMS Wiki Link: T. Boataabum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Discovered on Kakeg 29 S1, where they survive the dry and barren conditions. Nomadic in habit, their search for food takes them on a never-ending journey across this world. Delicate feeders, they nibble selectively at local flora, ensuring they never entirely strip an area of foliage.
NMS Wiki Link: X. Slashludoe - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found primarily on the grassy plains of planet Cuymed. Their movements are fidgety, darting this way and that in their desperation to eat but not be eaten. Their diet is rich in the Star Bramble found in abundance on this planet.
NMS Wiki Link: T. Bestseveus - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: A grasslands creature, at home in lush plains of planet Cuymed. Calm and methodical creatures, they graze the planet with an air of gentle, unflustered serenity. Their diet is varied, but they will gorge upon Star Bramble at any opportunity.
NMS Wiki Link: O. Ranaomboe - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found primarily on the grassy plains of Cuymed. Gentle, friendly creatures, they are always happy to interact with other living beings. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.
NMS Wiki Link: J. Xenozaloae - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found soaring over the temperate grasslands of planet Cuymed. Steadfast, with a strong sense of place, they pick a roost and will not abandoned {{sic}} their home unless facing certain death. Sharp sense and sharper claws allow them to tunnel swiftly through the earth in search of the tubers that form the bulk of their diet.
NMS Wiki Link: Y. Seedornum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found primarily in the humid, muggy skies of planet Cuymed. Nervous on the wing, they wheel and turn in endless loops, hoping to throw off any predators that might attempt to track them. Nocturnal tunnellers, they dig out elaborate tunnels in pursuit of nutritious tubers.
NMS Wiki Link: C. Sanguindecium - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: First discovered roaming the plant-filled landscapes of planet Cuymed. Quick, darting eyes reveal their nervous habit. They are quick to make decisions and even quicker to take flight. Herbivores, they feast upon the mineral-rich leaves of local plantlife.
NMS Wiki Link: J. Bumblepetrima - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on planet Cuymed, L. Doomoseum has adapted to the temperate climate and humid atmosphere. Cautious by nature. Even when facing starvation, they do all they can to avoid straying into unknown territory. Sharp vision allows them to detect seeds just as their {{sic}} begin to swell in their pods, giving them an edge over other foraging creatures.
NMS Wiki Link: L. Doomoseum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Y. Starnicis was first recorded in the shattered remains of planet Stvall Ganei, thriving despite the nuclear storms. Their search for food drags them far and wide across the planet, their journey never ending. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.
NMS Wiki Link: Y. Starnicis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on planet Stvall Ganei, where they had adapted to the hot, highly-radioactive atmosphere. Flighty, busy creatures, they are always on the move, always foraging for their next meal. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.
NMS Wiki Link: X. Grossubjica - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on planet Stvall Ganei, where they had adapted to the hot, highly-radioactive atmosphere. Shy, cautious beings, they will only descend from the sky to eat and drink in the dead of night. Though they have mouths, it seems their primary nutrient intake {{sic}} via their skin, in the form of atmospheric mineral absorption.
NMS Wiki Link: D. Xenomekia - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found in the radiation-blasted skies of planet Stvall Ganei. Sharp eyed and attentive, their vision is tuned to pick out the slightest movement on the ground beneath them. Highly specialised sense organs allow them to dig through the fecal deposits of other creatures, sniffing out and consuming the nutrients within.
NMS Wiki Link: N. Cobaltmosoe - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Discovered on Stvall Ganei, where they survive despite hostile levels of background radiation. Scans reveal a nervous system of pure light; the inner lives are radiant beyond compare. Nocturnal tunnellers, they dig out elaborate tunnels in pursuit of nutritious tubers.
NMS Wiki Link: H. Tapirwaposa - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Eshi 83 I5. Tough, hardy wanderers, they spend their lives on the move. Their existence is a constant, slow-moving race against predators and starvation. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.
NMS Wiki Link: E. Tamisyelamis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Eshi 83 I5. Always on the move, these nomadic grazers search far and wide for the perfect grazing sites. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.
NMS Wiki Link: Z. Felinuefae - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.
NMS Wiki Link: B. Succunesvae - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

There is very little in existence that might not kill them. A highly specialised digestive systems {{sic}} allows them to eat the Indium that grow on their home planet.

NMS Wiki Link: V. Skipunxeum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

NMS Wiki Link: I. Petalithsis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)
