NMS Wiki Link: M. Haloshippeus - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found on the wind-blasted plains of planet Kakeg 29 S1. These cautious fliers only take to the open sky when it is unavoidable, prefering {{sic}} to hug the terrain and flit between the cover of bushes and trees. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.
NMS Wiki Link: Z. Snaksevea - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: F. Rookxosis was discovered in the verdant landscapes of planet Cuymed. Long lives and a deep genetic memory give them an uncanny ability to predict future events. No famine or drought ever catches them by surprise. They delve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for the Cave marrow.
NMS Wiki Link: F. Rookxosis - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet Stvall Ganei. Their natural high stamina serves them well as they wander, walking countless miles in their search for food and shelter. Perpetual grazers, they consume vast amounts of grass each day.
NMS Wiki Link: U. Apisavonioe - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)
L. Bugxetresum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Eshi 83 I5. Calm and methodical creatures, they graze the planet with an air of gentle, unflustered serenity. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Indium that grow freely across this world.
NMS Wiki Link: A. Brociatusum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Eshi 83 I5. A careful hunter, they stalk their prey along long-distance migration routes. The weak are picked off as the journey wears them down. Well-adapted digestive systems allow them to find nutrients where others would give up. They happily feast upon the marrow of discarded bones, cracking them open and guzzling their nutritious cores.
NMS Wiki Link: V. Orangiziusmima - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

System: AGT Patron Saint of Lost Causes

Discovery Menu: Recorded in the poisonous rain and toxic air of planet Cagort Tau. Quick, darting eyes reveal their nervous habit; they are quick to make decisions and even quicker to take flight. A gnawing hunger for sugar drives their every waking moment; their existence a constant hunt from sweet plant to the next.
NMS Wiki Link: P. Cowuseum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Thrives on planet Cagort Tau, despite the constant acid rain. They appear to be peaceful creatures, happily socialising both within their species and without. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Fungal Cluster that grow freely across this world.
NMS Wiki Link: I. Starvoarea - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Highly adapted to the ferocious toxicity of its home, planet Cagort Tau. Bumbling and inattentive, they frequently find themselves trapped by both geological hazards and local predators. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.
NMS Wiki Link: P. Gerbillenica - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Secuset XI. A reckless predator, they happily hunt creatures far larger than themselves. Powerful, armour-plated tongues allow them to penetrate the toxic spiny shells of Venom Urchins. The rich green yolk within provides ample nutrients.
NMS Wiki Link: D. Darkgekkum - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Ukhumie Tau, where they survive despite the near-constant drought. Possessing a calm intelligence, their piercing eyes never forget a face. Comfortable amongst dense foliage, they sniff and scurry among fallen leaves, searching for the nuts that provide their food.
NMS Wiki Link: P. Magderae - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)
U. Aumphibiurplica - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)
O. Gulocimadica - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)
T. Hiydracudosa - No Man's Sky Wiki (fandom.com)

Appearance: A clump of bulbous body parts with thick pustules.

The creature is a large bug-like fauna with sickly-yellow chiten. The Non-Uniform version has a mushroom-like body with white accents, six compound eyes, hairs under the face, a mandible, and a thorax. The Prime version has a beatle-like body with green "jewels", crab claws, and blue eye stalks. Both genders have eight, spindly legs. The Non-Uniform version is the most common.
Discovery Menu: MIasma Spindlebug is at home in the toxic floods of planet Aagersf. Their soul responds to some rhythm deep within the planet's core, causing them to wander endlessly to its slow marching beat. Exceptionally fine teeth allow them to selectively eat, chewing only the most nutritious parts of otherwise tough and hard to digets plants.

Appearance: The creature is a huge crab-like fauna with pale white chiten and white stripes. The Asymmetric Gender variety has crab face and claws. The "Unknown" gender have six compound eyes with hairs underneath and spindly tentacles instead of claws. Both versions have a mushroom-like body. They also appear to be cousins with the Miasma Spindlebug, as the juvinle is extremely similar to one variation of the Miasma Spindlebug, implying that depending on the growth, the creature can be either or.
Discovery Menu: Thrives on planet Aagersf, despite the constant acid rain. These predators collaborate to attack in groups, communicating via a sophisticated combination of scents and vibrations. Carnivores, their hunger for Toxic meat knows no bounds.

Appearance: It resembles a small cluster of seven purple worms in a spiral formation, with each worm varying in size. Each worm glows that travels from the front tip to the rear tip.
Discovery Menu: This box is broken

Appearance: It resembles a grey-blue or green wheel made of bone and chiten.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on planet Ogori, where they thrive in the chokingly toxic atmosphere. Scans reveal small neural clusters growing all over their nervous system, creating a highly complex distributed brain network. They delve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for Cave marrow.

Summary Notes: Smallest dino I've found so far

Discovery Menu: Q. Trapamoe was recorded in the pale blue waters of planet Rias 14-T4. Gentle animals at heart, they wish only to be left in peace to roam. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

First recorded on planet Rias 14-T4, where P. Floesleum frolics in the water of its calm and sheltered seas. Their lives are short, and these saltwater fish spend their days in a desperate swim to find a willing mate. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

First recorded on planet Rias 14-T4, where G. Colookumus frolics in the water of its calm and sheltered seas. Large-eyed and with a swollen brain-sac, these fish appear to psses a wisdom that few sea creatures ever obtain. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Discovered on planet Rias 14-T4, K. Tyrantuilica swims freely in the temperate, bountiful water of its home seas. Carried by the currents as much as by their fins, their lives know no order, no system. They simply exist wherever greater forces have placed them. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

A forest creature, at home flitting in and above the rich canopies of planet Rias 14-T4. Fluttery and flighty, this creature spends its life airborne, too afraid to ever set down on land. They root through the undergrowth in search of food, chewing at the heads of ripe grasses.

Found on planet Rias 14-T4, where they roamed both forest and grassland. They seem aware of the constant danger in which they live, always scanning the horizon for new threats. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Found on planet Rias 14-T4, L. Heydroaynae has adapted to the temperate climate and humid atmosphere. Passive, they are happy to ignore most animal life unless forced by circumstance to pay attention. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Star Bramble.

Found primarily on the grassy plains of planet Rias 14-T4. Gentle animals at heart, they wish only to be left in peace to roam. Their diet consists of fallen fruit that has begun to rot. This fermented, bacteria-enriched mush appears to have a vital place in their digestive system.

Encountered roaming the hot and volatile plains of planet Rumuscar. Poor sensory systems leave this typically passive creature unable to perceive much of the external world. However, brain scans reveal a deep, rich inner life. They feast upon Condensed Carbon, and will travel vast distances to find it.

Spotted gliding above the volcanic plains of planet Rumuscar. Long lives, large brains, and canny, well-honed instincts give this creature the unmistakable air of wisdom. They root through the undergrowth in search of food, chewing at the heads of ripe grasses.

Discovered treading the surface of planet Rumuscar on thick-skinned feet. Their lives are brief; their existence a blip, nothing but a single desperate flight. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Encountered roaming the hot and volatile plains of planet Rumuscar. Possessed of a tremendous natural strength, they fear no other creature that walks upon this world. Herbivores, they feast upon the mineral-rich leaves of local plantlife.

The heat-resilient D. Rockputium is from planet Rumuscar. Social animals, they show great care in tending to their young and their sick. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly-coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.

Taxed by the burning atmosphere, B. Skipajum manages to endure on planet Rumuscar. Their gentle wingbeats belie their desperate hunger, their never-ending hunt. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Taxed by the burning atmosphere, W. Rattustaqea manages to endure on planet Rumuscar. Social animals, they show great care in tending to their young and their sick. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Condensed Carbon that grow freely across this world.

From the planet Cife, where they fight for survival amidst permanent sub-zero temperatures. Nervous on the wing, they wheel and turn in endless loops, hoping to throw off any predators that might attempt to track them. A highly specialised digestive system allows them to eat the Frostwort that grow on their home planet.

Well-adapted to their home planet, W. Galouedis easily copes with sub-zero temperatures. These cautious fliers only take to the open sky when it is unavoidable, preferring to hug the terrain and flit between the cover of bushes and trees. Gut analysis reveals their diet consists primarily of vast numbers of partially rotted nuts.

O. Grantkaus is found in the deep snow and icy forests of planet Cife. Highly intelligent for such a small animal, they appear to be entirely aware of their physical limitations. Their diet consists of fallen fruit that has begun to rot. This fermented, bacteria-enriched mush appears to have a vital place in their digestive system.

Found on planet Cife, home to harsh freezing winds. Without a centralised nervous system, these are creatures of pure instinct, pure reaction. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

From the planet Cife, where they fight for survival amidst permanent sub-zero temperatures. Highly intelligent for such a small animal, they appear to be entirely aware of their physical limitations. THey snuffle for food with their noses dug into the dirt, flickering earth into their mouths with long, spiked tongues. Nutrient source is presumed to be soil-bound microorganisms.

Q. Panothbiboe is found above the deep snow and icy forests of planet Cife. Scans reveal a nervous system of pure light; the inner lives are radiant beyond compare. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

L. Quarflorosa makes its home in the fields of planet New Plandpa. Patient and slow, they nibble and graze in perpetuity as they loll across the plains. They supplement their tuber-based diet with brightly-coloured flowers; the complex dye compounds providing a valuable micronutrient boost.

First discovered roaming the plant-filled landscapes of planet New Plandpa. Adrenaline glands embedded throughout the dermal layer suppress this beast's awareness of pain. Ill-equipped to compete with large animals, they choose to prey upon smaller foes. Rodents, insects, nitrogen-rich plantlife - anything unlikely to fight back.

Found on the planet New Plandpa, where the temperate climate and frequent rainfall encourage the rapid evolution of new lifeforms. Shy, cautious beings, they will only descend from the sky to eat and drink in the dead of night. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves

R. Beetbaiatima makes its home in the fields of planet New Plandpa. Nomadic in habit, their search for food takes them on a never-ending journey across this world. Sharp sense and sharper claws allow them to tunnel swiftly through the earth in search of the tubers that form the bulk of their diet.

First discovered roaming the plant-filled landscapes of planet New Plandpa. Patient by nature, they watch their prey carefully before striking, wasting no energy on failed hunts. Drawn to the smell of death, their primary nutrient source is Mordite. They do not discriminate between beast or plant.

A forest creature, at home flitting in and above the rich canopies of planet New Plandpa. Sharp eyed and attentive, their vision is tuned to pick out the slightest movement on the ground beneath them. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.

Y. Omnihoggium was recorded in the oceans of planet Pisburghe Prime, where the waters teem with an easy abundance denied to the sand-blasted surface. Large-eyed and with a swollen brain-sac, these fish appear to posses a wisdom that few sea creatures possess. They feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Found in the billowing dust of planet Pisburghe Prime. Their lives are painfully short, and these flying insects spend their handful of days in a furious quest to mate. Exceptionally fine teeth allow them to selectively eat, chewing only the most nutritious parts of otherwise tough and hard to digest plants.

Found on planet Pisburghe Prime, where R. Acansefollosa has adapted to the frequent swings in temperature. Once they have selected a nesting site, they remain there for the rest of their lives. As they continuously build, the nests of a mature adult are frequently colossal. Gut analysis reveals a varied but exclusively vegetarian diet.

Encountered in the waters of planet Pisburghe Prime, where the water maintains a steady warm in spite of the wild temperature swings of the surface world. Without a centralized nervous system, these creatures know nothing but swim, fight, flee, consume. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Encountered on planet Pisburghe Prime, where they survive despite the near-constant drought. Long lives and a deep genetic memory give them an uncanny ability to predict future events. No famine or drought ever catches them by surprise. Highly specialised sense organs allow them to dig through the fecal deposits of other creatures, sniffing out and consuming the nutrients within.

Discovered on Pisburghe Prime, where they survive the dry and barren conditions. Nervous and flighty, these creatures exist in a constant state of nervous excitement, ready to flee at the first sign of danger. THeir hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

Found on the wind-blasted plains of planet Pisburghe Prime. Submissive and gentle in their relationships with one another, they nonetheless respond forcefully when threatened by other creatures. Though they have mouths, it seems their primary nutrient intake is via their skin, in a form of atmospheric mineral absorption.

L. Serprovium was first recorded in the dustbowls of planet Pisburghe Prime. Their muscles are held in a state of constant tension, ready to flee at the smallest sign of danger. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

Recorded in the poisonous rain and toxic air of planet Toxet Beta. Possessed of a tremendous natural strength, they fear no other creature that walks upon this world. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Fungal Cluster that grow freely across this world.

Thrives on planet Toxet Beta, despite the constant acid rain. Inexhaustible, their wings never stop flapping. Their flight around the planet is never-ending. Leaf-eaters, their teeth are too soft to eat most vegetable matter. As such, they consume only soft, fresh leaves.

Encountered on planet Toxet Beta, where they live despite highly toxic conditions. Gregarious, wide-roaming creatures. They are occasionally found alone, but such animals are unhappy, lost from their herd. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

First recorded on the boiling acid planet Toxet Beta. They interact with their fellow beasts with a cheerful confidence, secure in the hierarchy of the herd. Their diet consists of fallen fruit that has begun to rot. This fermented, bacteria-enriched mush appears to have a vital place in their digestive system.

First encountered on the caustic landscapes of planet Toxet Beta. This predator fashions tools from their environment, conserving energy by automating their hunting process where possible. Omnivorous and thieving, they eat whatever they find, wherever they find it. Frequently, this means consuming the hard-won stores of other animals.

Discovered on Urniat Beta, where they survive despite hostile levels of background radiation. Powerful lateral muscles allow them to take off with remarkable speed, taking to the air faster than any ground predator could possibly lunge Gut analysis reveals their diet consists primarily of vast numbers of partially rotted nuts.

First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet Urniat Beta. Exceptionally strong, they appear to take delight in dismembering their prey. Is this emotion an illusion, or a sign of deeper intelligence? Row after row of highly-polished teeth allow them to tear through flesh and sinew alike. They can strip a corpose to the bone in minutes.

Found on planet Urniat Beta, where P. Seedzobilii thrives despite the never-ending radioactive glow. Sense organs appear unusually undeveloped for an apex predator. It seems to compensate by lashing out with extreme and indiscriminate violence. Dental analysis reveals jaws and teeth well-adapted to the ripping of flesh from bones, to the chewing life from other beings.

First recorded on the uranium-soaked landscapes of planet Urniat Beta. Their soul repsonds to some rhythm deep within the planet's core, cuasing them to wander undlessly to its slow marching beat. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest Gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Found on the radiation-blasted plains of planet Urniat Beta. Gentle creatures, though timid. They are reluctant to approach strangers, but display complex social behaviours within their herd. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Gamma Weed.

A. Xenohekoe was first recorded in the shattered remains of planet Urniat Beta, thriving despite the nuclear storms. Long lives, large brains, and canny, well-honed instincts give this creature the unmistakable air of wisdom. A plague upon stranded adventurers, as they feast upon di-hydrogen crystals. Their highly reactive saliva dissolves the crystals without the need to chew.

Thrives on planet Cagort Tau, despite the constant acid rain. Brain scans are unable to capture the true essence of their simple happiness. They snuffle for food with their noses dug into the dirt, flicking earth into their mouths with long, spiked tongues. Nutrient source is presumed to be soil-bound microorganisms.

First encountered in the caustic air of planet Cagort Tau. Sharp eyed and attentive, their vision is tuned to pick out the slightest movement on the ground beneath them. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

The host for this strange creature was found on planet Ulml Delta, lurking in the endless mounds of discarded shells. Gentle animals at heart, they wish only to be left in peace to roam. A forager, they search the ground for the fallen nuts that provide their main nutrient source.

J. Slapahysae makes it home in the fields of planet Ashik 88-P8. Exceptionally strong, they appear to take delight in dismembering their prey. Is this emotion an illusion, or a sign of deeper intelligence? They seek out larger creatures, prefering to make the one occasional kill and then feast upon it for months.

First discovered roaming the plant-filled landscapes of Ashik 88-P8. Nomadic in habit, their search for food takes them on a never-ending journey across the world. Sharp vision allows them to detect seeds just as their begin to swell in their pods, giving them an edge over other foraging creatures.

Encountered lurking in endless fractal dreams of planet New Dicenei. An unkind, jealous predator. They would sooner steal food from their own family than undertake a difficult hunt. After making a kill, they will preserve the blood of their prey in coagulated lumps. These stores serve them will during lean patches, times when their hunts go unsuccesful.

Encountered on planet Zethrap, where they survive despite the near-constant drought. Long-lived and gentle, their rich lives and complex society hirearchy allow them to develop wisdom that rivals technologically advanced species. Their blood is highly toxic to most predators, thanks to their oxide-rich diet.

Additional Notes: Ingredients obtainable from creature: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks
Discovery Menu: Torched by the extreme solar heat, F. Aamphibinanum survives on planet AGT Kema. Weaker than their appearance suggests, they make up for the many who die on their nomadic wanderings with frequent and rapid breeding. Perpetual grazers, they consume vast amounts of grass each day.

Additional Notes: Ingredients obtainable from creature: Crab Apple, Leg Meat
Discovery Menu: Discovered while exploring the overwhelming heat of planet AGT Kema. They seem aware of the constant danger in which they live, always scanning the horizon for new threats. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Solar Vine that grow freely across this world.

Additional Notes: Ingredients obtainable from creature: Leopard-Fruit, Feline Liver
Discovery Menu: Torched by the extreme solar heat, P. Coldtutium survives on planet AGT Kema. Powerful but submissive, they have evolved to avoid confrontation. Primarily a grazing animal, the poor nutrient levels of their grass-based diet leads them to seek out and lick mineral rich rocks.

Found soaring over the scorched plains of the planet AGT Kema. Highly intelligent, their brains are swollen, large out of all proportion to their body. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Solar Vine.

At home in the scorched landscapes of planet AGT Kema. Always on the lookout, their cautious nature reflects the sudden and violent cruelty of their own crude 'society'. Their tongues are razor sharp and lightning-quick, allowing them to catch and skewer the small insects that make up the majority of their diet.

Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Crab Apple, Leg Meat
Discovery Menu: Found on planet AGT Kema, sweltering in the baking heat. Scans reveal them to be highly intelligent. however, they are easily tamed and appear content to follow the whims of other creatures. Pugneum-infused theeth allow them to consume and digest gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Appearance: Paddlefish Head, Slender Body, big flat Side Fins, Scimitar Top Fin, Forked Tail.
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the seas of planet AGT Noyung, where it fights against the living oceans. These salt-water fish are pulled around the oceans by a gnawing hunger, a never-ending search for fresh food. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: Although no second sex has been identified to date, two forms of appearance have been documented: * Frilled Turtle-Head (olive and grass green), shark-tail. * Blank Turtle-Head with a vertical cervical flap, long pointed tail, big quills/spines on back. Both forms have an olive and turquoise green stripe skin pattern running from the forehead over the eye area to the tip of the tail. The area from the knees/elbows, as well as the beak and the entire lower jaw area are kept reddish brown. The front feet have four larger, sharp claws and a smaller, protruding, pointed thumb claw. The hind feet have three claws
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. This solo hunter is optimised for killing and eating. Their nervous system is focused purely on survival. Clean, fastidious eaters. They butcher the corpses of their prey, preparing each chunk of flesh on some instinctive schedule. They appear to reserve the hearts of their prey for consumption only during specific lunar phases.

Appearance: The two distinct appearances discovered were seen in both documented sexes: * Slug-Head (plum with sage eyes), grey table corals on back. * Long Fly-Head (black eyes, plum throat, black prongs on the back. Both appearances feature a split tail, rhino feet, and a type 2 (lizard-like) skin.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. Nervous and flighty, these creatures exist in a constant state of nervous excitement, ready to flee ant the first sign of danger. Perpetual grazers, they consume vast amounts of grass each day.

Appearance: The two distinct appearances discovered were seen in both documented sexes: * Feline-Head with fronds, seven shark-like spines on back (three in center and two on each side, running lengthwise) and small round elevations along these dorsal spines down to the Tail; splayed, pointed toe-feet with spine-like claws. Pointed wart-like bumps on the elbows; thick skin. The upper skin is uniformly colored grass green throughout - only the abdominal area has light and dark green stripes. * Reptilian-Head with antlers on it and with no visibal ears; a shell covering the whole back; feline-feet.; smooth skin. The grass-green coloring of the skin on the upper side of the body is covered with a dark green pattern of spots. The ventral side is gray with dots Both gender have a long Tail. The body is in shades of green, the mouth area and legs are greyish.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. An unkind, jealous predator. They would sooner steal food from their own family than undertake a difficult hunt. Carnivores, their desire for Venom Urchins knows no limits.

Appearance: Two appearances of this creature have been discovered. Both have a similar Evil-Eyed Peacock-Head, but differ greatly in gender, limbs, and body decorations.* The Symmetric gender is equipped with four Worm-Legs for locomotion and Razorfins on its back. The two larger eyes are located centrally, just above the fangs, while its two smaller eyes are adjacent to the larger ones on the left and right, respectively. * The Radical gender is shown with Beetle-Legs, Crab-Arms and a vertically grooved collar on the back. The two smaller eyes are directly above the fangs and the two larger eyes are to the left and right of them, respectively. Head and body decorations are ocher, the body and limbs are brownish. There are six visible spikes on the upper part of the back and one bump towards the head. Their compound eyes are cobalt blue.
Discovery Menu: J. Rhinoeyrica swims the tortured, fractal waters of AGT Noyung. They interact with their fellow beasts with a cheerful confidence, secure in the hierarchy of the herd. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: This creature owns a grey lizard-like skinned, armless Strider-Body with ten symmetrically arranged shark-like panels on the back and a Twin-Tail. The lower jaw is ocher. The two distinct appearances that were discovered were seen in both documented genders: * Strider-Flat-Head with two large, pointed, white horns on the forehead. Its black claws on its toes are smaller here. In the center of each tibia is an array of six black scales. The larger of the two toes is also scaled black. * Strider-Flat-Head with two large, flat, decorative Butterfly-Wing-Plates - one on the left and one on the right of the lower jaw. Its claws are white and larger. The scales on the shins and big toes are ocher in color. Both forms (the one with the horns and the one with the plates) were seen with two sharp fangs in the upper jaw.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Tall Eggs, Strider Sausage.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. A dangerous hunter, their sense organs appear to swell as they detect the stress hormones of their prey. They prefer to acquire their meat from sources that will not fight back. Quick jaws and sharp eyes allow them to prey upon the small, darting creatures that other hunters leave behind.

Appearance: On the planet AGT Noyung, the being O.Waterhabus was sighted in two forms of appearance. Both forms have smooth, wart-like, round elevations. The back is well defined from the rest of the body. The extremities are plum-colored. The beak of the bird-head creature is teal in both sighted forms. O.Waterhabus has frog feet and a small tufted tail. Two different forms of appearance have been documented: *White bumps on the back, three plum-colored longitudinal keels on the head. Predominantly plum colored body with a longitudinal ocher stripe from forehead to tail tuft and an ocher belly. The fluffy tail tip is plum colored. *A light teal back with a darker spotted pattern and plum bumps on it. The defined edge of the back is plum colored. Head and tail are teal in color. O.Waterhabus was spotted more likely around monuments and plaques. So far, despite the two different appearances, no second sex has been found.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. Social animals, they show great care in tending to their young and their sick. They feast upon Emeril, and will travel vast distances to find it.

Appearance: A Butterfly(Eagle)-Winged Flying Lizard. The Bird-Head has a large crest on top and a smaller crest on the bottom of the head. The tail is divided into three flat parts, the middle part being the larger (Eagle-Tail). Along the bare, thin neck, starting from the head crest up to the level of the shoulder blades, are dark scales. The featherless body is kept entirely in grey tones. Sunlight breaks through the thin skin of the wings and the veins are clearly visible. An external difference could not be determined in the two sexes.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet AGT Noyung. Shy, cautious beings, they will only descend from the sky to eat and drink in the dead of night. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Emeril.

Appearance: Paddlefish Head, Slender Body, two large, elongated narrow Side Fins and two small and short but wide Side Fins, Scimitar Top Fin, Crescent Tail.
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the seas of planet AGT Noyung, where it fights against the living oceans. Without a centralised nervous system, these creatures know nothing but swim, fight, flee, consume. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: A creature with Rodent-Head and two big but flat Ibex-Horns on it. Four heavy Elephant-Feet carry the most weight and a thin pair of Two-Claw-Feet gives the last boost. Both genders have a Round Tail. One form though appears with a shell on the back and the other form with Slices. Shell and Slices are brownish. This creatures skin is thick, mostly green on back, tail, and shoulders. Scales appear on the front feet. Abdomen and mostly the whole underside of the body seems grey and cream. The eyes of this creature are big and completely black.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Fresh Milk, Raw Steak
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet Noyung. They are cautious, watchful dreatures; their teeth are too soft to eat most vegetable matter. As such, they consume only soft, fresh leaves.

Appearance: Two forms of gender and appearance of the greenish Eyeball-Body Lok(Blob)-Creature have been spotted. One form appears with arms and its conifer green Plantleave-Head bears a lilac blooming flower. The other form appears with a Thorn-Head that bears four large, thick thorns, standing in a circle to each other, and two smaller thorns, sticking out to the side. The colour of the thorns is warm grey.  The head wreath appears plum-colored in both forms.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Noyung. Drawn by magnetic forces on long journeys across the planet, their lives are spent in constant motion. They snuffle for food with their noises dug into the dirt, flicking earth into their mouths with long, spiked tongues. Nutrient source is presumed to be soil-bound microorganisms.

Appearance: Although the Creature Discovery Menu shows a Toucan-Head, One-Saw-Winged Agnelis - this form of appearance was not seen in either the northern or southern hemispheres nor in between during the exploration of the planet AGT Noyung. Instead two genders of Ant-Head, Double-Saw-Winged Agnelis were sighted and scanned. It is assumed that the observed biological form of appearance will eventually supplant or may have supplanted the other. However, more detailed investigations are still pending. What the two forms have in common is their Stump-Tail.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet AGT Noyung. Long-distance fliers, their migratory routes take them from pole-to-pole in their search for food. Primarily a grazing animal, the poor nutrient levels of their grass-based diet leads them to seek out and lick mineral rich rocks.

Appearance: This Bone Serpent Prionterrae has a silver-blue head shield, four long pink-white gradient tentacles for locomotion, and two dorsal stumps (above the locomotion limb). After another research expedition, which took place five months after the first, the divergent species named V. Picacontima, linked to F. Tremoxigeum, was sighted - in two different genders: Unknown and Rational. Both species show the same appearance and behaviour.
Discovery Menu: Found wandering the fevered, dreamlike landscape of planet AGT Luxem. These flying insects are drawn ever onwards by a terrible hunger, their hunt is never ending. They delve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for the cave marrow.

Appearance: Wraith-like eel with a worm head with a large round maw studded with teeth. Its body consists of two distinct segments, each with two barbs on the abdomen and six smaller spines on the back. In addition, each segment has two smaller fins and a small dorsal fin. Its caudal fin is long and has two streamlined top and bottom fins that extend from the end of the body to the end of the tail (eel tail).
Discovery Menu: Found in the haunted depths of planet AGT Luxem. Their eyes never close, for they never sleep. Their swim is endless, unbroken by rest or respite. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: Although the bat-like appearance seems uncharacteristic for a butterfly species, this small member of the Rhopalocera genus flies in small flocks just above the ground. The all-red mini bat, with its pointed-eared bat head, segmented fish wings, and glider tail, is found all over the planet. Its skin is finely scaled.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet AGT Luxem. Without a centralised nervous system, these are creatures of pure instinct, pure reaction. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

Appearance: This very small gar-headed fish, with its round body, round tail, scimitar top fin and four small rear side fins, swims in small shoals in the waters of AGT Luxem. These fishes appear very curious, but flee quickly.
Discovery Menu: Encountered in the deep waters of planet AGT Luxem, where N. Xenomasteum is carried by endless looping currents. Inexhaustible, their fins never stop moving. Even a few moments of calm would rob their gills of the flow they need to live. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: This lively member of the Sporefly family, with its red leaf-wings and ocre-brown tendrils, flies low in smaller swarms over the planet's surface.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet AGT Luxem. These flying insects are drawn ever onwards by a terrible hunger, their primary nutrient intake via their skin, in a form of atmospheric mineral absorbtion.

Appearance: Beautifully colored in green and purple, this earless bat-headed air-acrobat tirelessly flies across the breathtaking world of AGT Luxem with its thin-skinned segmented fish-wings. Its double-lanced tail helps it balance itself perfectly. Only one form of appearance could be sighted.
Discovery Menu: Found soaring in haunted, mournful skies of planet AGT Luxem. Temperamental, evvervescent creatures. They swirl through the air with a wild and beautiful unpredictability. A gnawing hunger for sugar drives their every waking moment; their existence a constant hunt from sweet plant to the next.

Appearance: This eel-like, eel-headed aquatic creature with gill-eel-body, finless and equipped only with a narrowly fanned dorsal top fin, glides in circles through the depths of the waters of AGT Luxem. Its forked, pointed tail is probably more for decoration than for drive. The gray patterned skin is impressive.
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the seas of planet AGT Luxem, where it fights against the living oceans. Their lives are brief; their existence a blip, nothing but a single desperate thrash against great global currents that carry them. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: A Bikokus is constantly doing its rounds on AGT Futiapon as a loner. It moves on seven independent disks or rollers. It is interesting that the individual locomotion elements do not rotate in the same direction at the same time. The direction of movement (forward or backward) of each element is opposite to that of adjacent elements. It is assumed that the middle, largest, rotary element specifies the actual main direction and the lateral discs are used for fine adjustment. A. Bikokus was documented with an indeterminate gender. The color of the locomotion parts seems to be golden yellow, dark sand. The transitions between the elements could consist of a flexible lubricant - in terms of color, the transitions stand out with a dark copper hue. After another research expedition, which took place five months after the first, the divergent species named W. Jacklegustima, linked to A. Bikokus, was sighted in scan mode instead - in two different genders: Indeterminate and rational. Both species and genders show the same appearance and behaviour. The Creature Discovery Mode displays the overview for both species under the name description A. Bikokus.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Bone Nuggets, Lumpy Brainstem.
Discovery Menu: Found on the gamma-drenched surface of planet AGT Futiapon. Remarkably hight endurance means they rarely stop moving, able to gaze endlessly as they migrate across the planet. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

Appearance: This swimming cow comes with a cute melon face and teddy bear ears. Its two front feet are elephant-like and it has two two-clawed hind feets. The tail is round and smooth. The entire back is decorated with black calcite slices. The skin color is mainly olive green with some black streaks. All legs show grass-green scales on the front side. The neck has an olive green button collar. The melon in the face is big and rusty red. The eyes are wide open, olive green, with a cream colored pupil. The entire lower abdomen and inner ear area appear greyish. They are only found in groups and the groups themselves are not far apart. Two genders could be discovered. They share the same form of appearance.
Discovery Menu: D. Felinokiium was found in the oceans of planet AGT, where the water is as irradiated as its nuclear-blasted surface. Carried by the currents as much as by their fins, their lives know no order, no system. They simply exist wherever greater forces have placed them. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: D. Quadovea appears in a worm-like eel body, predominantly red and ocher. Two appearances have been sighted: * Worm-like eel body with a flat rear-facing double shield that attaches to the forehead and extends over the nape, and beady black eyes. *Wormlike eel body with laterally protruding ear-like skin flaps and a stalked eye that could serve as antennae. This creature is often found in small groups.
Discovery Menu: D. Quadovea was first recorded in the shattered remains of planet AGT Futiapon, thriving despite the nuclear storms. They appear to be peaceful creatures, happily socialising both within their species and without. They delve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for the cave marrow.

Appearance: A symmetrical gender of E. Bearsolveum was first discovered. After another research expedition, which took place five months after the first, the divergent species named H. Terraeffea, linked to E. Bearsolveum, was sighted in scan mode instead - in two different genders: Symmetric and Indeterminate. Both species and genders show the same form of appearance and behaviour. The Creature Discovery Mode displays the overview for both species under the name description E. Bearsolveum.
Discovery Menu: First recorded on the uranium-soaked landscapes of planet AGT Futiapon. Their lives are painfully short, and these flying insects spend their handful days in a furious quest to mate. Their hunger is only sated by the chunky, fleshy roots of the mordite plant.

Appearance: On the planet AGT Futiapon, two genders of the creature F. Ranaaiesiium were sighted. It seems, that the appearance depends on the gender. Both form of appearances have a bird head with visible ears and three keels, bear legs, a shark tail, a ridge on the back and a coarse, long fur. They only differ in the pattern of the fur and in the shape of the ridge and keel. *The fur is striped in rust-red and tan, the ridge on the back appears copper coloured, round and smothed (but with cracks), the three keels on the head are striped too. *The fur is symmetrically mottled with large areas of rusty red and white, the ridge on the back  has a rough saw blade edge and is tan coloured like the keels.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks.
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet AGT Futiapon. Secure in their own strength, this predator often appears calm and docile. They will only snap into action when provoked, or hungry. Gut analysis reveals an iron-rich, carnivorous diet. Their stool is dense and mighty.

Appearance: Only one gender and one appearance was initially observed of this worm-like, mostly dirty cream-colored, black eyed and sharp-toothed creature. After another research expedition, which took place five months after the first, a second gender and form of appearance was sighted. It is interesting that so far only the first documented form of appearance has been observed to appear in both discovered genders. The two form of appearances differ in the following ways: *Worm-like eel body with two laterally protruding, white skin flaps with saw blade structure. *Worm-like eel body with dark tan quills on the back.
Discovery Menu: Found on planet AGT Futiapon, where L. Coldjoea thrives despite the never-ending radioactive glow. Long lives and a deep genetic memory give them an uncanny ability to predict future events. No famine or drought ever catches them by surprise. Though they have mouths, it seems their primary nutrient intake via their skin, in a form of atmospheric mineral absortion.

Appearance: The pineapple-like creature has eight black, always open, eyes   four eyes in front and four eyes behind. The transition to the decorative main ornament appears knotted and overgrown. The main body is round and aquamarine in colour. The transition to the headdress is dirty red and ocher. The leaves stand out in rich green. The creature is crowned by an upright single flower. The following lines contain observed and documented details about the leaves and the flower: *Fern-like unipinnate (imparipinnate), compound flat but large feathery leaves, comb-shaped overall picture, arrow-shaped points directed backwards. *The flower runs from light green around the center to plum at the edge. Flower center and flower stalk are orange.
Discovery Menu: Found on the radiation-blasted plains of planet AGT Futiapon. Yielding quickly in direct confontation, their non-threatening nature is a successful counter-strategy in an aggresive world. Perpetual grazers, they consume vast amounts of grass each day.

Appearance: The pineapple-like creature has eight black, always open, eyes   four eyes in front and four eyes behind. The transition to the decorative main ornament appears knotted and overgrown. The main body is round and light tan in colour. The transition to the is light brown and light green. The leaves stand out in rich green. The creature is crowned by an upright single funnel-shaped flower with a ribbed edge. The two discovered sexes differ in their leaf and flower decoration. The following lines contain these documented details about the leaves and flowers. Model 1: *Lance-like, large and fleschy, green leaves. *Funnel-shaped flower with a ribbed edge and a gradient from yellow in the center to orange at the ragged edges of the petals. Model 2: *Fern-like bipinnate (imparipinnate), compound flat small and fine and narrow rowed, feathery leaves; The fern leaves in the center are moss green, the colored leaves at the edge appear plum-colored. *Flower with eight individual, overlapping petals and a gradient from yellow in the center to the round orange petal edges.
Discovery Menu: Found on the gamma-drenched surface of planet AGT Futiapon. Calm and methodical creatures, they graze the planet with an air of gentle, unflustered serenity. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.

Appearance: The creature M. Dasyludeum is always busy piercing the ground of AGT Futiapon. Initially, only one gender could be documented: vectorized. After another research expedition, which took place five months after the first, the divergent species named G. Cerytilanium, linked to M. Dasyludeum, was sighted in scan mode instead - in two different genders: Vectorised and None. Both species and genders show the same appearance and behaviour. The Creature Discovery Mode displays the overview for both species under the name description M. Dasyludeum. Three rows of ribs (each consisting of seven flexible ribs) rotate in and around each other, constantly, to enable perpetual locomotion. The radius of the Dreierlei narrows towards the head end. The inner skin of each rib appears flesh-colored and the outer skin is bright green.
Discovery Menu: Found on planet AGT Futiapon, where they had adapted to the hot, highly-radioactive atmosphere. These simiple insects barely have a brain at all and react to external stimuli only via localised reflexes. Their finely-luned sense of smell draws them to the most beautiful, richly-scented flowers, which they then consume whole.

Appearance: There were two genders of the creature O. Falconxonima sighted. It seems, that the appearance depends on the gender. Both form of appearances have a bird head, rodent legs, and a short rounded tail. Their leathery skin is mostly grass green and brown. The appearances only  differ in the texture of their skin and their head- and back-decoration:  *The leathery dark brown and mostly grass green skin is covered with mocha-colored flat bumps, there is a dark brown ridge on the back. *The leathery skin is covered with lightbrown horn web, and the predominantly grass-green skin shows through in the web's round, flat dimples. The two horns of the dorsal crest are mocha colored and the skin connecting the horns and the creature's back is grass green.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Wild Milk, Meaty Chunks
Discovery Menu: First recorded in the irradiated atmosphere of planet AGT Futiapon. Their search for food drags them far and wide across the planet, their journey never ending. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.

Appearance: T. Ornikasilae flies over AGT Futiapon with bat wings and bat head, really bat-like and very gallant. Its double lance tail is perfect for maintaining balance and making fantastic maneuvers. The ears are always pricked, so this creature never misses a sound. The body feathers are soft. The creature's color is primarily mocha. The abdomen appears light brown. A bit of ocher shimmers through here and there on the wings and legs.
Discovery Menu: Encountered on AGT Futiapon, where they have adapted to the nuclear catastrophe that enveloped the planet. Long lives, large brains, and canny, well-honed instincts give this creature the unmistakable air of wisdom. A highly specialised digestive systems allows them to eat the Gamma Weed that grow on their home planet.

Appearance: Paddlefish head, round body, crescent tail, spiky upper fin and a second big (rear) side fin - this small fish is almost impossible to see or catch. It has black streamlines on its dark and light brown body. Curiously, an average height of -0.0 m was determined!
Discovery Menu: X. Stonweruris was first encountered in the irradiated seas of planet AGT Futiapon. No matter the size of their shoal, the lack of any communicative organs leave these fish with a profound sense of loneliness. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of organisms.

Encountered roaming the hot and volatile plains of Ilyanneti III. Long lives and a deep genetic memory give them an uncanny ability to predict future events. No famine or drought ever catches them by surprise. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Condensed Carbon that grow freely across this world.

Appearance: Bat head, Butterfly wings, Double lance tail
Discovery Menu: Suited to swamplike conditions, A. Radiovirae is found on worlkds hight in moisture and humidity. Powerful lateral muscles allow them to take off with remarkable speed, taking to the air faster than any ground predator could possibly lunge. A highly speciallised digestive system allows them to eat the Star Bramble that grow on their home planet.

Appearance: Paddlefish head, Slender body, Forked tail, Scimitar top fin, Wideflat side fins
Discovery Menu: B. Talosdaileus thrives in the slimy waters of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Carried by the currents as much as by their fins, their lives know no order, no system. They simply exist wherever greater forces have placed them. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Appearance: Bat head, Bat wings, Ant tail
Discovery Menu: Happy in humid conditions, D. Scarceoe is found in the steamy atmosphere of planet Sadallestin Ungo. When the light begins to fade and the shadows stretch out acreoss the hills, this soulful and intelligent being takes to the sky to sing, their sweet music tumpling down behind them. They feast upon Star Bramble, and will travel vast distances to find it.

Appearance: Model 1: Crab head, Spider-Crab body, no arms, 4 Spider legs, Razorfins Accessory. Model 2: Peacock head, Spider-Crab body, 2 Tendril/Worm arms, 8 Tendril/Worm legs, Ant tail.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Crab Apple, Leg Meat. Since predominantly large mammels are preferred as food and no larger terrestrial animals were discovered on Planet Sadallestin Ungo, cannibalistic behavior cannot be ruled out.
Discovery Menu: E. Campimasus nests in the humid swamps of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Highly territorial, this predator continually marks their hunting grounds with scent. Pheromones are undetectable by herbivore species. They seek out larger creatures, prefering to make the one occasional kill and then feast upon it for months.

Appearance: Model 1: Blob body, Auricles and Antennae above the mouth, Striped skin with indicated donut knobs. Model 2: Tri-pachycephalo head, 8 Sspider eyes, no arms, Striped skin with small donut knobs.
Discovery Menu: Preferring a moist climate, H. Hopulkamia is at home in the swamps of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Friendly and curious by nature, they will take a keen interest in any new lifeforms they encounter. Drawn to sugar, they consume the small fruits that fall from local flora.

Appearance: Large Butterfly with: Moth body, Standard Frontwing, no Midwing, Leaf Backwing. Wings mainly light purple with green inner line and little green spots on the Leaf Backwing. The Moth body is mainly light purple with a turquoise longitudinal stripe on top.
Discovery Menu: An air-dwelling creature, H. Slyueoe was discovered above the swamps of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Carried by the wind as much as their wings, these small insects [sic] live a scattered and chaotic existence. They dwelve underground in search of food, and show a particular fondness for the cave marrow.

Appearance: Dragon-headed Loach/Eel/Sea Snake. Loach Body with Ribbon Fins and a short eel tail.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Salty Fingers; Only the second gender, discovered about a year later, produces Wild Milk - which cannot be extracted/harvested.
Discovery Menu: Discovered swimming in the murky oceans of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Their eyes never close, for they never sleep. Their swim is endless, unbroken by rest or respite. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Preferring to keep dry, N. Sweetebatium mostly dwells in the skies of its swampy home planet Sadallestin Ungo. Scans reveal a nervous system of pure light; the inner lives are radiant beyond compare. Filtering gills inside their cheeks allow them to suck up water and extract nutrients from algal blooms.

Appearance: The tendrils that grow from the five broad, wedge-shaped sections of the elongated, segmented body, glow bluish.
Additional Notes: Creature-derived ingredients: Dirty Meat; First discovered by the Traveller Duolagong in 2022, the species name had been saved in the fauna discovery screen as "R. Oustridunus". The re-scan, many months later, by a different traveller, showed the different name "F. Quadzizeum" - although the gender(s) and other notes remained the same.

Appearance: Bone driller in bone and fleshlike colours.
Discovery Menu: S. Brickohea nests in the humid swamps of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Their gentle wingbeats belie their desperate hunger, their never-ending hunt. Always hungry, they seek out and consume the Star Bramble that grow freely across this world.

Appearance: Loach headed Loach/Worm/Sea Snake, with an eel body, no fins, but a forked tail.
Discovery Menu: V. Folysesheum was discovered in the deep waters of planet Sadallestin Ungo. Without a centralised nervous system, these creatures know hothing but swim, fight, flee, consume. Scavengers, they feed upon the soft downward drift of plankton; feasting upon the dying remains of tiny organisms.

Discovered amidst the thermonuclear fog of planet Xeterrel Tau. Once secure in a territory, they appear to tend to local plantlife, bolstering their own food supply. They root through the undergrowth in search of food, chewing at the heads of ripe grasses.

V. Luxnesutima was first recorded in the shattered remains of planet Xeterrel Tau, thriving despite the nuclear storms. Their lives seem spent in constant anxiety, they are tense and fearful even on a genetic level. Constantly hungry, their specially adapted teeth and guts allow them to consume entire trees, from leaf to sap to trunk.

Appearance: Rectangular / cuboid shape, floats and spins around its axis. Brown / tan in colour.
Discovery Menu: The host for this strange creature was found on planet Otechke XIV, lurking in the endless mounds of discarded shells. Highly intelligent, they remember every encounter they ever have with another species. Highly specialised sense organs allow them to dig through the fecal deposits of other creatures, sniffing out and consuming nutirents within.

Appearance: Flying insectoid style creature with a long slender body and two large wings (like a butterfly). Bright green in pigmentation with dark, forest green spots across wings (likely to replicate large eyes to ward of predators).
Long slender body, wings like a bat, small head with beady eyes. Yellow/red pigmentation.

Long slender body with swollen abdominal sack (like a spider). Two wings with four limb sections, shaped like a butterfly's wings. Black, oval shaped eyes with two head antenae. Sand coloured pigmentation with green highlights along assumed skeletal structure.
Creative with 5 arrow-head shaped exo-skeletal body parts (on average), with tenticles protruding from each section. No obvious eyes. Soft grey/off-white in pigmentation.
Giant flying worm-style creature with a circular, toothed mouth and horns protruding from the mouth edges. Brown pigmentation.
Bipedal animal with back spines, hooves, and a snout / eyes like a feathered bird.

Creature wqith long, pointy tail, beak like face and small eyes, with feathered head. Huge wings (each wing larger than its body, wing-span likely double it's body). Clawed feet. Black and grey striped pigmentation with deep purple highlights (probably bone structure highlights).
A winged bat-like creature with webbed tan coloured wings, a green body, and a striped green and tan bee-like abdomen. Black eyes. Black snout. Large green ears.
A brown and dark tan coloured winged creature with a hook style beak, beady black eyes, and claw like feet. Long body, very over-sized wings.
A yellow and grey coloured winged creature with four thin, fly-like wings (two on each side of the body), claw styled feet, a beak, black beady eyes and a rounded head.
A light blue honeycomb structured animal with a glowing purple centre. Circular in structure.
A teal coloured creature with four hooved legs, a long dual tail, curly horns, petite snout, and brown finns on its back.
A winged creature with brown and dark red feathers. Large wings. Large beak in proportion to its body. Abdomen-like tail.
A green and red striped, coloured creature with four hooved legs, a long dual tail, curly horns, petite snout, and green finns on its back.

A four legged creature with stumpy, angled legs, four toes on each leg, and what looks like a primary head and a secondary? head? Dark brown, tan, and white coloured with stripes. Round primary head with sharp rows of teeth, large nostrils.

A large beetle like flying creature with a very large claw/mandible/horn on the front of its head (might be its head). Looks to have small beady eyes on lower horn. Four yellow wings, two long wings, two short wings. Murky grey in colour.
A four winged feathered bird with green, blue, and sand brown markings. Long beak, two legs with visible talons.
A light blue toned star shaped being with small porus holes and a soft pink sphere at its core.
A dark grey, purple and white bird with four wings, a long tail, and purple beak.
A snow white and off white coloured bird with four feathered wings and a tail. Two large black feet with talons. Long oval shaped ears, short snout, and beady eyes.
A quadripedal animal with a hard teal green and soft purple exoskeleton, featuring light blue crystal growths.
A bipedal animal with a dark grey/blue tinged exoskeleton. Back features four protruding spines. Large abdominal tail, two hind arms, small cap-like head.

A quadripedal animal with four large, hoofed legs, small stumpy tail, armoured black back carapace, and elongated head. Features a large, hinging mouth, small beady inset eyes. Is primarily white and brown in colour with striped pattern.
A winged animal that features a black and light blue feathered body, long tail, and legs with talons. Wings are webbed, beak is long and black, eyes are small and beady.

A quadripedal biological entity with a vine like skeletal structure, with plant-like growths across its spine. Head is disguised, or possibly could consist of, flower-like formations. Skeletal structure is a deep brown colour. Growths alternate between light yellow, soft orange, and soft brown in colour.

A stumpy quadripedal creature with thick, leathery, waxy hide for skin that is light brown, tan, and dark brown in colour. Tail is round and featureless. Back features one continuous fin. Legs feature 4 toes each with black nails/hoofs. Head is pointed and shielded by a thick layer of skin. Mouth and teeth are exposed at the end of the head. Eye location unknown.

W dark blue and soft murky yellow feathered bird. Features four insect like wings with thin skin membrane. Huge, thin, pointed tail used for gliding and balance. Small beady eyes and a small black beak.

A very long, spin covered worm-like creature that is able to fly high in the atmosphere. Estimated to have in the region of 40 leg-like formations on either side of the worm-like body. These move independtly of the worm's movement. Centipede-like in nature. Head is protected by two rows of thick spines. Mouth is small, feautring many teeth and mandibles. Is light tan/sand coloured.

A quadripedal biological entity with a vine like skeletal structure, with plant-like growths across its spine. Head is disguised, or possibly could consist of, flower-like formations. Skeletal structure is a light green and brown colour. Growths alternate between light yellow, soft red, green, and soft brown in colour.
Brown, textured sphere with spherical bars encompassing its body structure. Off-white circles on body surface.
A disk shaped flying animal with a grey/brown leathery top-skin and soft yellow underbelly.

A large bug with six red, translucent legs, three on each side of its torso. Boulboud carapace with horns protruding from each side of an abdomen, with a final tail spike at its rear. Mid-section is dark brown has fluid sacks containing light red/orange liquid (possibly an egg sack). Head is a rough pyramid shape, moss green with three dark, compound eyes on each face. Three curved horns protruding from front of head. Mouth location unknown.

A flying bird-like animal with snow white coloured skin and fur, with a slight light mint green tint. Has two wings, webbed, extending from mid point of torso and one long tail. Has fur on torso, two feet with claws, and a black, armoured beak covering the entire front of its head. Has two black, beady eyes.

A quadripedal animal with a dark brown and red tough fur coat. Has a broad tail about half of body length on average. Back features a patterened shell-like structure. Pattern features irregular dark brown oviods against the shell-like structure's light red base. Features four to five toes on each foot, each foot has a paw. Head is comparitvely small for body. Mouth thin with razor sharp teeth. Strange red sacks on side of neck for an unknown purpose, potentially scent glands.

A winged animal that features a multi-coloured feathered body. Head and torso are dark red, cream, and dark grey in colour. Underside of body is a lighter shade of red than head (perhaps to blend with habitat and avoid predators). Features two wings with very large feathers that taper towards the ends as they evolve into a shade of green.

A winged animal that features a multi-coloured feathered body. Head is dark grey in colour, as is body (with tan coloured highlights). Features a dual pronged tail that is grey and red in colour, two feet features claws, head with mandibles and antenae and large black beady eyes. Wings are feathered and primary cream coloured with light grey and green patterning.

Two legged animal with two large claaws on each paw. Has hind legs, two tails, and a feathered brown and green fur coat. Head has fanned skin membrane extending out the top of its head, two black, small, beady eyes, gilled snout.

A very small winged animal (about the size of a standard humanoid hand palm) that has a dark and bright green colourings. Does not have fur, but rather a leathery skin-like outer skin organ. Has webbed wings, a short tail that extends from the body, and a small head that fatures mandibles, small bead-like eyes, and tiny antenae.

A large quadripedal animaly with large front legs and skinny hind legs. Has a large tail with feathered/spined, bulbous end. Has hunced back structure, with long, large spines on the top of its back. Head is small in comparison to body size, features large circular ears, small round eyes, spines on top of head, small snout. Dark grey and brown in colour.

A large quadripedal animal withshort front legs and long hind legs. Has a short tail with a bulbous end. Has angled back structure towards head with two webbed fins on back. Head is small in comparison to body size, features pointy ears sticking out top of head, tiny eyes protected by bone lumps on brow, small snout nose and long mouth. Blue, black, and green in colour.

A large quadrapedal animal. Has hoofed feet (black hooves), large belly on underside, hunch on back with glowing crystal growths. Has long neck with snout, beady inset eyes. Is a deep wine red and beige colour; has leathery skin.

A large spherical creature with a reflective, pearlescent body tone featuring a green and slightly red tint. Surface of creature seems to be a form of liquid. Unsure how creature retains its structure. Floats gently through the air like a balloon.

A quadripedal animal with no flesh, fur, skin. Formed entirely of a skeletal structure. Has hooved feet, a balled tail with sharp spines, a ridged back, large boulbous head, and two large protruding horns at the front of its face.

Discovery Menu: Discovered while exploring the overwhelming heat of planet Naxo. Gentle, friendly creatures, they are always happy to interact with other living beings. Spoor analysis reveals a high-fibre diet. Primary nutrient source appears to be excavated plant roots.

Appearance: A light green bird with a darker shade of green stripes with a bat head.
Discovery Menu: From the planet Naxo, where they struggle daily against the scorching temperatures. Long lives, large brains, and canny, well-honed instincts give this creature the unmistakable air of wisdom. A specially-adapted tongue indicates their diet is predominantly nectar, harvested from local flora.

Found wandering the scorched plains of the planet Naxo. Passive, they are happy to ignore most animal life unless forced by circumstance to pay attention. Pugneum-infused teeth allow them to consume and digest gravitino balls, crunching through their outer shells in an explosion of light.

Despite the fierce heat, M. Mulochmiforius survives happily on planet Naxo. They appear to be peaceful creatures, happily socialising both within their species and without. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Solar Vine.

Appearance: Brown sphere with holes that resemble craters
Discovery Menu: Found on planet Naxo, sweltering in the baking heat. Cautious by nature. Even when facing starvation, they do all they can to avoid straying into unknown territory. Sharp visions allows them to detect seeds just as they begin to swell in their pods, giving them an edge over other foraging creatures.

Discovered on the sun-battered surface of planet Naxo. Their muscles are held in a state of constant tension, ready to flee at the smallest sign of danger. Their tongues are hairy and thick, allowing them to happily chew upon all but the most venomous of leaves.

Discovered on the sun-battered surface of planet Naxo. These predators collaborate to attack in groups, communicating via a sophisticated combination of scents and vibrations. Extremely powerful carnivores, they sit atop the food chain. Nothing dares to hunt them.

Specially adapted to the unimaginable heat, P. Underrozoe was first encountered on planet Naxo. Gentle creatures, though timid. They are reluctant to approach strangers, but display complext social behaviours within their herd. Gut analysis reveals a diet consisting almost entirely of Solar Vine.

Specially adapted to the unimaginable heat, U. Taxlavicis was first encountered on planet Naxo. Shy, cautious beings, they will only descend from the sky to eat and drink in the dead of night. They use their acidic tongues to burrow into trees, dissolving and then sucking out the soft and delicious inner wood.

Found wandering the fevered dreamlike landscape of planet Keyaksha Delta. A crafty hunter, known to kill the young of competing species. Powerful, armour-plated tongues allow them to penetrate the toxic spiny shells of Venom Urchins. The rich green yolk within provides ample nutrients.

Found wandering the fevered , dreamlike landscape of planet Keyaksha Delta. Quick, darting eyes reveal their nervous habit; they are quick to make decisions and even quicker to take flight. They use their acidic tongues to burrow into trees, dissolving and then sucking out the delicious inner wood.
